      "type": "ValidationResult",
      "name": "Velocity field comparison against PIV measurements at design point",
      "description": "Axial and radial velocity profiles extracted from RANS CFD solution compared against particle image velocimetry (PIV) data at the design operating point (5 L/min, 3500 RPM). Spatial-average RMS error of 4.2% relative to bulk velocity. Experimental uncertainty in PIV derived from ensemble statistics over 500 image pairs; CFD iterative convergence verified to residual norms below 1e-6.",
      "hasUncertaintyQuantification": "https://uofa.net/synth/uq/uq-velocity-piv-ensemble"
    },
    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/validation/vr-hemolysis-index",
      "type": "ValidationResult",
      "name": "Relative hemolysis index validation across operating envelope",
      "description": "Predicted normalized index of hemolysis (NIH) values computed from Lagrangian particle-tracking stress accumulation compared against in-vitro hemolysis measurements for 5 flow-speed combinations. Predicted RH values range 0.71–0.94 against experimental RH range 0.68–0.97. Inherent variability in biological blood samples assessed qualitatively by the assessment team; batch-to-batch variation in erythrocyte fragility was noted as a source of aleatory uncertainty but was not formally characterised through a structured uncertainty quantification analysis. The absence of a structured UQ link for this result reflects the practical limitation that inter-donor hematocrit variability was described only in narrative form."
    }
