    "actor": "https://uofa.net/synth/actor/morrison-credibility-team",
    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "All 7 assessed credibility factors meet or exceed required levels for MRL 2. The 6 not-assessed factors are acceptable at MRL 2 per ASME V&V 40-2018 Table 3. Predicted RH values range 0.71–0.94 across all 5 operating points, satisfying the RH < 1 acceptance criterion with margin. The CFD model is judged credible for identifying worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for the Class II CPB device. Note: aleatory uncertainty in hemolysis index validation arising from inter-donor blood sample variability was characterised qualitatively; a structured uncertainty quantification was not linked to the hemolysis-index validation result.",
